CSS Rule

1. Selector
2. Declaration block {property: value;}
Eg
p {
    color: blue;
    text-align: center;
}

Methods
1. In-line CSS. Disadvantages are that they are messy and can crowd large projects
2. Internal CSS
3. External CSS Can be used for multiple pages

Selector
1. Element Selector. Targets all instances of an element.
eg 
p {
    font-size: 16px;
}

2. ID Selector(id is a unique identifier)
Eg
html: <div id="unique">Unique box</div>

changes to
CSS styling: 
#unique {
    border: 1px solid black;
}

3. Class Selector (*)
Eg
html: <p class="highlight">This is highlighted!</p>

changes to
CSS styling:
.highlight {
    background-color: yellow;
}
4. Universal Selector

Padding is the space between css element content and border
Margin is the space outside a border and another border of an element
